## DECISION LOG

[Decision 1] Anchor Framework
- Why: Current Solana standard, excellent tooling, good docs
- Alternative considered: Pure solana-program (too verbose)

[Decision 2] Next.js App Router
- Why: Modern, server components, fast dev iteration
- Alternative considered: Vite (less ecosystem for Solana)

[Decision 3] shadcn/ui + Tailwind  
- Why: Component library + utility CSS = speed
- Alternative considered: Material-UI (heavier, more opinionated)

[Decision 4] Mock Data > RPC Calls (Phase 1)
- Why: Devnet RPC can be flaky; mock data = predictable testing
- Plan: Phase 2 swaps mocks → real RPC queries

## BLOCKERS / UNKNOWNS

⚠️ Build Time
- Next.js first build: ~90-120 seconds (expected)
- Cargo not in sandbox: Solana program can't compile yet
- **Decision**: Code is ready; compile in Phase 2 on real dev machine

⚠️ Wallet Adapter Defaults
- Phantom requires user browser extension
- Fallback: Prompt install if wallet not found
- Testnet: Can use devnet without testnet SOL balance

